<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF386A87F8239D9217A0B611" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF386A87F8239D9217A0B611" blockId="195.[2014,2611,2900,3324]" lastBlockId="195.[1401,2607,3330,3482]" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F7849D9216CCB0DA" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[2168,2252,3019,3048]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F7189D921751B0DA" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2276,2385,3019,3048]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">muricola</taxonomicName>
species group. Previously treated within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F6A39DB717C7B73D" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[2399,2503,3054,3087]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="959" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
nugax. Genetic studies place this species as sister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F7B69A1C1705B76C" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[2122,2309,3141,3166]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
; these two may be most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F6CF9A3D17D4B7B7" baseAuthorityName="Gray" baseAuthorityYear="1846" box="[2355,2516,3172,3205]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="970" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muricola">M. muricola</taxonomicName>
, or to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F81C9AD5166AB79F" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[2016,2154,3212,3245]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pilosus">M. pilosus</taxonomicName>
and M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F70E9AD51764B79F" box="[2290,2404,3212,3245]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chinensis">chinensis</taxonomicName>
, and perhaps 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F8239AEA16AAB7E6" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1874" box="[2015,2218,3251,3284]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montivagus">M. montivagus</taxonomicName>
. Relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF386A87F6319AEA1433B7E6" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[2509,2611,3251,3284]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="959" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
and M. munricola 1s unclear; all three occur in Borneo, where respective species limits require further study. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF386A87FA859B7319ACB6A8" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF386A87FA859B7319ACB6A8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398876" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398876" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398876/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="957" targetBox="[1399,1991,2910,3324]" targetPageId="195">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF386A87FA859B7319ACB6A8" blockId="195.[1401,2607,3330,3482]" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF386A87FA859B731829B679" bold="true" box="[1401,1577,3370,3403]" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Distribution.</emphasis>
N &amp; W Borneo; only known from three localities in 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFF386A87F6E49B73176BB679" box="[2328,2411,3370,3403]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Sabah</collectingRegion>
(Gomantong Caves, Baturong Caves, and Sinoa) and recently found in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF386A87F75B9B081719B640" box="[2215,2329,3409,3442]" name="Malaysia" pageId="195" pageNumber="957">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
(Bukit Sarang, Bintulu division); may be more widespread.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3F6A80FF4E97701B65BF65" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3F6A80FF4E97701B65BF65" blockId="196.[177,1385,297,1512]" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF3F6A80FF4E97701FADBA70" bold="true" box="[178,429,297,322]" pageId="196" pageNumber="958">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Tail 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FE0497701C8DBA70" box="[504,653,297,322]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.05" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="40.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="36.0">36-45 mm</quantity>
, ear 12:6—15- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FCB297701DA0BA70" box="[846,928,297,322]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
, hindfoot 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FBCB97701AAABA70" box="[1079,1194,297,322]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8-9 mm</quantity>
, forearm 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FACB97701F16BA5B" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="41.5" valueMax="43.0" valueMin="40.0">40- 43 mm</quantity>
; weight 6-4-8- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FE1F97111C10BA5B" box="[483,528,328,361]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="8.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="g" value="8.0">8 g</quantity>
. Differs from Peters’s 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FCB497111DA1BA5B" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[840,929,328,361]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FC4497111A17BA5B" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[952,1047,328,361]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ater">M. ater</taxonomicName>
) in longer forearm and skull; feet small. Dorsal fur has blackish bases and dark brown tips; underparts are dark brownish gray with black hair bases; there is a golden-brown patch in center of belly, as in its sister species, the Hairy-faced 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FD5D97E71CFABAED" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[673,762,446,479]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FCED97E71DC8BAED" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[785,968,446,479]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="annectans">M. annectans</taxonomicName>
). Ears are medium-sized, with anterior margin convex and a rounded tip; tragus is narrow, c.40% ear length, with slightly concave anterior margin and more strongly convex posterior margin, with a marked triangular lobe at its base. Wing membrane is attached at base of toe; calcar is long and narrow toward tip, with a narrow keel. Skull is long and not especially broad, with inflated braincase and shallow frontal depression; no conspicuous sagittal crest. Skull is much narrower and less massive than in the Bornean Whiskered 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FAD994F21ED0B9C1" authority="Kaup, 1829" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FF16948B1F79B9C1" authorityName="E. H. Taylor" authorityYear="1934" box="[234,377,722,755]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="967" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="browni">M. browni</taxonomicName>
). C' is short, roughly equal to or slightly shorter than posterior upper premolar; P? is small, equal to or smaller than I’, and displaced slightly inward; P* is greatly reduced, less than quarter the surface area of P* and displaced inward, so that P* and P* are in contact; C, is small, ¢.20% shorter than P, and ¢.40% smaller than that tooth in surface area; P, is not particularly small, about half the height of canine, and about one-and-a-half times the surface area of I,, completely in line in tooth row; P, is tiny, completely displaced inward so that P, and P, are in contact or nearly so; P, is about the same height as M,. Differs from Peters’s 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF3F6A80FC8695BE1DD4BF3A" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[890,980,999,1032]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
in greater reduction of middle premolars, and in the small canines which are similar in length to P*, and distinctly shorter than P,. Condylo-basal length 14-3-15- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FCC1926F1D90BF65" box="[829,912,1078,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
; maxillary tooth row 5:6- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3F6A80FB11926F1B61BF65" box="[1261,1377,1078,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="196" pageNumber="958" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="6.0">6-9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
